The paper discusses the creation of a temporal knowledge graph and its application in biographical timeline generation. This involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of large-scale knowledge graphs and RDF representation, which are related to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
